In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event. To force a theme, set `Application.Current.UserAppTheme`.

```csharp
// Detect current system theme
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified

// Subscribe to real-time theme changes
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");
    // Update UI or re-apply styles here
};

// Force a specific theme (overrides system setting)
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**A more structured approach** — a theme service you can inject via DI:

```csharp
public class ThemeService
{
    public void Initialize()
    {
        Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += OnThemeChanged;
    }

    public AppTheme Current =>
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme != AppTheme.Unspecified
            ? Application.Current.UserAppTheme
            : Application.Current.RequestedTheme;

    public void SetTheme(AppTheme theme) =>
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = theme;

    public void FollowSystem() =>
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;

    private void OnThemeChanged(object sender, AppThemeChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"System theme changed: {e.RequestedTheme}");
        ThemeChanged?.Invoke(this, e.RequestedTheme);
    }

    public event EventHandler<AppTheme> ThemeChanged;
}
```

**Key points:**

| Property / Event | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `RequestedTheme` | Read the OS-level theme |
| `RequestedThemeChanged` | Fires when the OS theme toggles |
| `UserAppTheme` | Override the theme app-wide |
| `UserAppTheme = Unspecified` | Revert to following the system |

In XAML, you can also use `AppThemeBinding` to declaratively swap resources:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />
```

This updates automatically when the theme changes — no code-behind needed for simple color/style swaps.
